Teltoli squeezed her eyes tighter shut as she heard Carnage's wake up 
call, and groaned mildly, moving a paw in her friends direction as if 
to make her stop that noise. In reality her paw only moved a few 
inches or so along the ground, but the small sound stopped and 
Teltoli relaxed.

Figuring that she was now awake, she sighed and cracked open one eye 
to see the dawn coming up, and groaned even louder in dissapointment. 
It was only the beginnings of dawn! The Fuzor then opened both eyes 
and assumed that she was to get up then. The few minutes earlier had 
been done on pure instinct.

She slowly sat up, fluffing her wings up from where they had been 
crushed against the ground. The Fuzor looked around and saw that 
Carnage was no where to be seen.

Scanning around the forest, her scanners picked up that Carnage was 
somewhere near, merely sitting. Teltoli lowered her brows in 
confusion, but shrugged and looked around at the scenery.

Everything looked.. fresher, if that was possible. Morning dew 
glistened from the rays of light that were just beginning to come up, 
mist travelling slowly across the ground with oh-so-slight winds. A 
smile crept across her face. Definatly better than Cybertron mornings.

Looking up to see a rather tall tree beside her, under which the boar 
had been buried, she grinned and unsheathed her claws. Part of her 
form was a panther, and they were natural tree climbers! Putting one 
paw on the wood, she felt her sharp claws dig in and gain a grip, so 
she quickly climbed up the tree, using all four paws. Getting up to 
the lowest, but sturdiest branch, she lay down in typical panther 
fashion and let her wings hang down. 

Teltoli looked in the direction that her scanners said Carnage was, 
and wondered if her friend was getting ready for the training, or 
deciding what she would do. She grinned a little and started to relax 
her own mind, almost a form of meditaton, but still alert.
